{"title_page": "Baa Baaa Black Sheep", "text_new": "{{For|the [[nursery rhyme]]|Baa, Baa, Black Sheep}}\n{{short description|2018 film directed by Vishal Pandya}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| film name      = {{film name|Hindi|}}\n| name           = Baa Baaa Black Sheep\n| image          = Baa Baaa Black Sheep.jpg\n| alt            = Baa Baaa Black Sheep Official Poster\n| caption        = Official Poster\n| director       = Vishwas Paandya \n| producer       = Anand Swarup Agarwal<br />Krishna Datla<br/> <br/> Agastya Films\n| writer         = Sunjiv Puri  <br/>\n                   Vishwas Paandya <br />\n| starring       = [[Manish Paul]]<br />[[Anupam Kher]]<br />[[Manjari Phadnis]]<br />[[Annu Kapoor]]<br />[[Kay Kay Menon]]\n| music          = <small>'''Songs:'''</small><br>[[Shaan (singer)|Shaan]]<br/>Roshan Balu<br/>Gourov DasGupta\n| cinematography = Amalendu Chaudhary\n| editing        = Bakul Matiyani\n| studio         = Super cassets industries ltd.<br />Agastya Films <br /> \n| distributor    = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| runtime        = 103 minutes\n| released       = {{Film date|2018|03|23|df=y}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n}}\n\n'''''Baa Baaa Black Sheep''''' is a 2018 Indian [[Action film|action]] [[Comedy (film)|comedy]] film,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/baa-baaa-black-sheep-teaser-is-out/articleshow/62791092.cms|title='Baa Baaa Black Sheep' teaser is out|date=5 February 2018|work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsx.com/entertainment/baa-baaa-black-sheep-trailer-anupam-kher-shines-in-this-confusing-dark-comedy|title=Baa Baaa Black Sheep trailer: Anupam Kher shines in this confusing dark-comedy|date=7 February 2018|publisher=News X}}</ref> starring [[Anupam Kher]], [[Manish Paul]], [[Annu Kapoor]], [[Manjari Phadnis]] & [[Kay Kay Menon]] in a lead roles. The film is directed by Vishwas Paandya and produced by Anand Swarup Agarwal & Krishna Datla while it's presented by Soham Rockstar. The film was released on 23 March 2018.\n\n==Plot==\nBaa Baa Black Sheep is the story of Baba, who is still trying to find his bearings. Baba's father, Charudutt Sharma who is a boring Cashew nut dealer for everyone, reveals to a shocked Baba on his 25th birthday that actually they are a family of hit men since the past 12 generations, and now Baba has to take over as the 13th. On the other hand, Baba's love interest Angelina runs a Beach Cafe. Her father Brian Morris is a retired art teacher, but fuels his greed for money and excitement, by selling fakes of an old Renoir painting that his family has inherited. With Baba and Angelina, both keeping their respective secrets, problems start when Kamya, an art gallery owner, wants the original Renoir and blackmails the Home Minister, Utpal Shivalkar for it. Drugs, Contract killings and blackmail account for ACP Shivraj entering the scene trying to find out the connection between all the chaos.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Manish Paul]] as Baba\n* [[Anupam Kher]] as Charudutt Sharma/Charlie\n* [[Manjari Phadnis]] as Angela Morris\n* [[Annu Kapoor]] as Brian Morris/Santa Claus\n* [[Kay Kay Menon]] as A.C.P Shivraj Naik\n* [[Natasha Suri]] as Kamya\n* [[Manish Wadhwa]] as Utpal Shivalkar/Home Minister\n* [[Mamta Verma]] as Manju Sharma\n* [[B. Shantanu]] as Kamaal\n* [[Vineet Sharma]] as Daniel D'Costa\n* [[Aakash Dabhade]] as Johny Fixer\n* [[Kirthi Shetty]] as Jamaal\n* Scarlett Mellish Wilson as item number \"Galla Goriyan\"\n\n==Soundtrack==\nGalla Goriyan / Aaja Soniye \u2013 The first song of the film is recreated by [[Gourav-Roshin]] which is based on Abhijit Vaghani's Mashup from The [[Super Cassettes Industries T-Series|T-Series]] Mixtape Punjabi.\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline=Track listing\n| extra_column=Singer(s)\n| total_length= 18:29\n| title1= Galla Goriyan / Aaja Soniye\n| extra1=[[Mika Singh]], [[Kanika Kapoor]]\n| length1= 3:53\n| lyrics1= [[Jalees Sherwani]], [[Babbu Maan]]\n| music1=Superbia (Gourov-Roshin & Shaan), [[Jaidev Kumar]], [[Sajid\u2013Wajid]]\n| title2= Heer\n| length2= 3:40\n| extra2=Mika Singh, [[Mahalakshmi Iyer]]\n| lyrics2=[[Rajesh Manthan]]\n| music2= Superbia (Gourov-Roshin & Shaan) \n| title3= Baa Baaa Black Sheep\n| length3= 3:16\n| extra3=[[Shaan (singer)|Shaan]], [[Manisha Chakravaty]]\n| lyrics3=[[Sunil Sirvaiya]]\n| music3=Superbia (Gourov-Roshin & Shaan)\n| title4= Angelina\n| length4= 4:19\n| extra4=[[Sonu Nigam]]\n| lyrics4=Sunil Sirvaiya\n| music4=Superbia (Gourov-Roshin & Shaan) \n| title5= Ram Leela\n| length5= 3:21\n| extra5=[[Kumar Sapan]]\n| lyrics5=Rajesh Manthan\n| music5=Superbia (Gourov-Roshin & Shaan) \n|all_writing=|title6=|length6=|title7=|length7=|title8=|length8=|title9=|length9=|title10=|length10=|title11=|length11=|title12=|length12=|title13=|length13=|title14=|length14=|title15=|length15=|title16=|length16=|title17=|length17=|title18=|length18=|title19=|length19=|title20=|length20=}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|5598578}}\n* [http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/baa-baaa-black-sheep/Baa Baaa Black Sheep] at [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:Indian action comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:T-Series films]]\n\n\n{{2010s-Hindi-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 film directed by Vishal Pandya}}\n{{For|the [[nursery rhyme]]|Baa, Baa, Black Sheep}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date= February 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| film name      = {{film name|Hindi|}}\n| name           = Baa Baaa Black Sheep\n| image          = Baa Baaa Black Sheep.jpg\n| alt            = Baa Baaa Black Sheep Official Poster\n| caption        = Official Poster\n| director       = Vishwas Paandya \n| producer       = Anand Swarup Agarwal<br />Krishna Datla<br/> <br/> Agastya Films\n| writer         = Sunjiv Puri  <br/>\n                   Vishwas Paandya <br />\n| starring       = [[Manish Paul]]<br />[[Anupam Kher]]<br />[[Manjari Phadnis]]<br />[[Annu Kapoor]]<br />[[Kay Kay Menon]]\n| music          = <small>'''Songs:'''</small><br>[[Shaan (singer)|Shaan]]<br/>Roshan Balu<br/>Gourov DasGupta\n| cinematography = Amalendu Chaudhary\n| editing        = Bakul Matiyani\n| studio         = Super cassets industries ltd.<br />Agastya Films <br /> \n| distributor    = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| runtime        = 103 minutes\n| released       = {{Film date|2018|03|23|df=y}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n}}\n\n'''''Baa Baaa Black Sheep''''' is a 2018 Indian [[Action film|action]] [[Comedy (film)|comedy]] film,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/baa-baaa-black-sheep-teaser-is-out/articleshow/62791092.cms|title='Baa Baaa Black Sheep' teaser is out|date=5 February 2018|work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsx.com/entertainment/baa-baaa-black-sheep-trailer-anupam-kher-shines-in-this-confusing-dark-comedy|title=Baa Baaa Black Sheep trailer: Anupam Kher shines in this confusing dark-comedy|date=7 February 2018|publisher=News X}}</ref> starring [[Anupam Kher]], [[Manish Paul]], [[Annu Kapoor]], [[Manjari Phadnis]] & [[Kay Kay Menon]] in a lead roles. The film is directed by Vishwas Paandya and produced by Anand Swarup Agarwal & Krishna Datla while it's presented by Soham Rockstar. The film was released on 23 March 2018.\n\n==Plot==\nBaa Baa Black Sheep is the story of Baba, who is still trying to find his bearings. Baba's father, Charudutt Sharma who is a boring Cashew nut dealer for everyone, reveals to a shocked Baba on his 25th birthday that actually they are a family of hit men since the past 12 generations, and now Baba has to take over as the 13th. On the other hand, Baba's love interest Angelina runs a Beach Cafe. Her father Brian Morris is a retired art teacher, but fuels his greed for money and excitement, by selling fakes of an old Renoir painting that his family has inherited. With Baba and Angelina, both keeping their respective secrets, problems start when Kamya, an art gallery owner, wants the original Renoir and blackmails the Home Minister, Utpal Shivalkar for it. Drugs, Contract killings and blackmail account for ACP Shivraj entering the scene trying to find out the connection between all the chaos.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Manish Paul]] as Baba\n* [[Anupam Kher]] as Charudutt Sharma/Charlie\n* [[Manjari Phadnis]] as Angela Morris\n* [[Annu Kapoor]] as Brian Morris/Santa Claus\n* [[Kay Kay Menon]] as A.C.P Shivraj Naik\n* [[Natasha Suri]] as Kamya\n* [[Manish Wadhwa]] as Utpal Shivalkar/Home Minister\n* [[Mamta Verma]] as Manju Sharma\n* [[B. Shantanu]] as Kamaal\n* [[Vineet Sharma]] as Daniel D'Costa\n* [[Aakash Dabhade]] as Johny Fixer\n* [[Kirthi Shetty]] as Jamaal\n* Scarlett Mellish Wilson as item number \"Galla Goriyan\"\n\n==Soundtrack==\nGalla Goriyan / Aaja Soniye - The first song of the film is  recreated by [[Gourav-Roshin]] which is based on Abhijit Vaghani's Mashup from The [[Super Cassettes Industries T-Series|T-Series]] Mixtape Punjabi.\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline=Track listing\n| extra_column=Singer(s)\n| total_length= 18:29\n| title1= Galla Goriyan / Aaja Soniye\n| extra1=[[Mika Singh]], [[Kanika Kapoor]]\n| length1= 3:53\n| lyrics1= [[Jalees Sherwani]], [[Babbu Maan]]\n| music1=Superbia (Gourov-Roshin & Shaan), [[Jaidev Kumar]], [[Sajid\u2013Wajid]]\n| title2= Heer\n| length2= 3:40\n| extra2=Mika Singh, [[Mahalakshmi Iyer]]\n| lyrics2=[[Rajesh Manthan]]\n| music2= Superbia (Gourov-Roshin & Shaan) \n| title3= Baa Baaa Black Sheep\n| length3= 3:16\n| extra3=[[Shaan (singer)|Shaan]], [[Manisha Chakravaty]]\n| lyrics3=[[Sunil Sirvaiya]]\n| music3=Superbia (Gourov-Roshin & Shaan)\n| title4= Angelina\n| length4= 4:19\n| extra4=[[Sonu Nigam]]\n| lyrics4=Sunil Sirvaiya\n| music4=Superbia (Gourov-Roshin & Shaan) \n| title5= Ram Leela\n| len